Rating: 4
I have lived in Maryland nearly 20 years all told and I never had tried to cook soft-shell crabs. This recipe is SO good and SO easy! To clean crabs yourself takes about 30 seconds: (1) cut off the eyes and mouth with a sharp scissors, (2) lift up the upper shell on either side and sweep out the "gills" with your finger, and (3) remove the "apron" on the underside (the pointy hard thing). I did add 1 tsp of Old Bay seasoning to the flour before dredging. I skimped on the clarified butter and was sorry because any little bits of solid non- clarified butter will burn. Even so the dish was delicious and a huge hit. This is definitely going to become a new specialty of mine, and this is my go-to recipe.

