Quick, easy, tasty. I'm allergic to milk, so soaked crabs in water. Added a little cayenne, salt and pepper to the dredging flour. Deglazed the pan with a little white wine with the lemon juice. Don't actually think you need the extra butter, but what the hell? I think the key to this is great, ultra-fresh crabs.

